</div></section></section><section id="S12"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">Comorbid Conditions</h3>
<p id="P18">Comorbidity was common. In 2003–2008, more than half of patients with heart failure had hypertension (73%), hypercholesterolemia (54%), or arthritis (62%) (<a href="#T2" class="usa-link">Table 2</a>). Nearly half had a history of myocardial infarction (48%) or were obese (47%).</p>
